to be in good condition with some signs of wear here and there but we had been pointed out in advance We took a long test drive and tested everything When we returned we handled the sale and left our other car behind We received a decent price for both our old car and new car Negotiation was no problem After this back to the north After about an hour the car started to stall and stopped Since it was after 1700 we called the ANWB who read and reset the error message After this we could go home without too many problems Upon arrival at home we immediately emailed AMS automotive and informed us of our return journey We received a neat email back that we should have the car read out at a garage in the area and keep AMS automotive informed about the progress The car went to the dealer on problemsIn short there are really car dealers who know how to do it We were biased from the past But in the end they were helped very satisfied at AMS automotive Very friendly quick response via email
